<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="152" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1060,1519]" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,315,1276,1302]" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[351,611,1276,1302]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xiaojinensis">
<emphasis box="[351,611,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Saussurea xiaojinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<emphasis box="[753,774,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">S.</emphasis>
subgen. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Candolle" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Cassini" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[883,1231,1276,1302]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Lagurostemon">
<emphasis box="[883,997,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Saussurea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1070,1231,1277,1302]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Lagurostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
owing to its welldeveloped stems, caudex not fibrously split, capitula numerous, and leaf blade oblong or lanceolate. The species is distinct in its leaves sessile, base semiamplexicaul, decurrent into stems forming wings. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Maximowicz (1881: 495)" authorityName="Maximowicz" authorityPageNumber="495" authorityYear="1881" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvatica">
<emphasis box="[1322,1452,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">S. sylvatica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Maximowicz, C. J." box="[136,421,1384,1411]" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" pagination="425 - 560" refId="ref6861" refString="Maximowicz, C. J. (1881) Diagnoses plantarum novarum asiaticarum. IV. Bulletin de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences de Saint- Petersbourg 27: 425 - 560. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 46308" type="journal article" year="1881">Maximowicz (1881: 495)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance but differs in several characters (see 
<tableCitation box="[1084,1166,1384,1410]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="11.[136,224,1565,1589]" captionText="TABLE 3. Comparsion of Saussurea xiaojinensis sp. nov. and S. sylvatica." pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Table 3</tableCitation>
for the detail). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. S. Chen" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xiaojinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Saussurea xiaojinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[653,701,1420,1446]" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">type</typeStatus>
locality, i.e. Xiaojin, Sichuan, 
<collectingCountry box="[1048,1118,1420,1446]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">China</collectingCountry>
, growing at altitudes between 2840 and 
<quantity box="[244,329,1456,1482]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" unit="m" value="2900.0">2900 m</quantity>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maximowicz" authorityYear="1881" box="[437,564,1456,1482]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvatica">
<emphasis box="[437,564,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">S. sylvatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs widely in 
<collectingCountry box="[757,824,1456,1482]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[839,913,1456,1482]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Gansu</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[923,993,1456,1482]" country="China" name="Hebei" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Hebei</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1003,1096,1456,1482]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1105,1198,1456,1482]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1208,1289,1456,1482]" country="China" name="Shanxi" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Shanxi</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1345,1435,1456,1482]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
), growing at altitudes between 1600 and 
<quantity box="[576,661,1492,1519]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" unit="m" value="4500.0">4500 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[675,832,1492,1518]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" unit="m" value="3750.0" valueMax="4300.0" valueMin="3200.0">3200–4300 m</quantity>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[868,963,1492,1519]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="11" pageNumber="152">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
